9 Hours Ago The former Customs boss is survived by one wife and three children –two sons and a daughter. He attended Government College, Kaduna in 1974 where he obtained the West African Senior School Certificate Examination in 1980. He had a Bachelor of Science degree in Economics and a master's degree in Finance from the University of Dimitrov Apostle Tshenov, Svishtov, Bulgaria. He joined the Nigeria Customs Service in 1988 and was the CG of Customs from 2009 to 2015.